## What you just got

```
crawlhub/crawlers/{{platform_name}}/
├── __init__.py
├── plugin.yaml              # manifest — declares actions & schemas
├── service.py               # dispatch layer (R3: keep thin)
├── README.md                # this file
└── crawler/
    ├── __init__.py          # public entry point: re-exports {{scraper_class}}
    ├── scraper.py           # business orchestration (yields dicts)
    ├── client.py            # HTTP / network layer
    ├── models.py            # @dataclass + to_dict()
    └── _internal/           # platform-private helpers (sealed by R3)
        └── __init__.py
```

The generated scaffold ships with one trivial action — `ping` — purely so
that `pytest tests/test_platform_conformance.py` passes immediately. Your
first real edits should:

1. Add your real actions to `plugin.yaml` (replace `ping`).
2. Choose each action's `runtime`, `transport`, and `throttle_scope`.
3. Add matching `@dataclass` types to `crawler/models.py`.
4. Implement those actions as public methods on `{{scraper_class}}`
   (`crawler/scraper.py`), each writing `Model(...).to_dict()`.
5. Move network protocol details into `crawler/client.py`.

