## Common errors and what they mean

| Error                                                                | Cause                                                          | Fix                                                            |
|----------------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| `C2: action='X' is missing output_dataclass`                         | New action added to yaml without `output_dataclass`            | Add `output_dataclass: "<your.models>:Class"`                  |
| `C3: action='X' field mismatch`                                      | Dataclass fields drifted from `output_schema`                  | Make them equal (modulo `_source_*`)                           |
| `C4/C5: imports from crawler._internal.*`                            | `service.py` / `bridge.py` reaches into private helpers        | Re-export the helper via `crawler/__init__.py`                 |
| `C6: forbidden directory 'output/'` (etc.)                           | You wrote artifacts into the package tree                      | Use `ctx.output_dir` instead                                   |
| `C7: ctx.write_record(asdict(...))` / inline-dict write              | Bypassing the dataclass contract                               | Build a `@dataclass`, call `.to_dict()` on it                  |
| `C8: dataclass ... has no to_dict()`                                 | New dataclass forgot the method                                | Add a `def to_dict(self) -> dict:` returning `asdict(self)`    |
| `C9: ... Path(__file__) together with a write API`                   | Writing inside the package                                     | Switch to `ctx.output_dir` or `get_data_root()`                |
| `C10: yaml declares actions [...] but service.py does not dispatch`  | You added a yaml action without a matching scraper method      | Add the method (`getattr` dispatch handles the rest)           |
| `C21: transport=websocket must declare ...`                         | WSS action lacks explicit stop inputs                          | Add `duration_seconds` and `stop_when_room_closed` inputs      |
